The paper discusses a security technique (code randomization) and its impact on a specific type of attack (JIT-ROP), which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses methodologies for measuring the effectiveness of code randomization, which could fall under software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the impact of code randomization on the expressive power of payloads, which could fall under systems and control (cs.SY) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
